P# Azure Inactive Users Checker

A PowerShell script that connects to Microsoft Graph and identifies enabled users who have not changed their password in 90 or more days. Works without an Azure AD Premium licence.

---

## What It Does

1. Connects to Microsoft Graph using your admin account
2. Fetches all **enabled** users from your Azure AD tenant
3. Flags users whose **password has not changed in 90+ days**
4. Displays results in the terminal and saves them to a CSV file

> **Why password change date?** Azure AD's actual last sign-in date (`SignInActivity`) requires a Premium licence. This script uses `LastPasswordChangeDateTime` as a no-cost alternative.

---

## Requirements

- Azure Cloud Shell (PowerShell mode) at [shell.azure.com](https://shell.azure.com)
- An admin account with one of the following roles:
  - **Global Administrator**
  - **Global Reader**

---

## Permissions Required

The script requests the following Microsoft Graph scope when you sign in:

- `User.Read.All`

---

## First Time Setup

Run these in Cloud Shell **before** running the script for the first time:

```powershell
Install-Module Microsoft.Graph -Scope CurrentUser -Force -AllowClobber
```
> Takes 2–5 minutes to complete. Only needs to be done once.

---

## How to Run

### Step 1 — Create the Script File
```powershell
code inactive-users.ps1
```

### Step 2 — Paste the Script
Paste the full script into the editor and press **Ctrl + S** to save.

### Step 3 — Run It
```powershell
./inactive-users.ps1
```

### Step 4 — Sign In
A browser popup will appear — sign in with your **admin account** and grant the requested permissions.

### Step 5 — Download the Results

Click the **⬆⬇** button in the Cloud Shell toolbar, select **Download**, and enter:
```
inactive-users.csv
```

---

## Output

Results are shown in the terminal and saved to `inactive-users.csv` with the following columns:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| `DisplayName` | User's full name |
| `UserPrincipalName` | User's email / login address |
| `LastPasswordChange` | Date the password was last changed |
| `LicenceAssigned` | Whether the user has a licence (`True` / `False`) |

---

## Adjusting the 90 Day Threshold

To change the inactivity period, edit this line in the script:

```powershell
$cutoff = (Get-Date).AddDays(-90)
```

For example, change `-90` to `-60` to flag users inactive for 60 days or more.

---

## Troubleshooting

| Error | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Get-MgUser not recognised` | Run `Import-Module Microsoft.Graph.Users` then retry |
| `Assembly already loaded` conflict | The script handles this automatically with `Remove-Module` at the top |
| `403 Forbidden` | Your account is missing the required role — check you have Global Reader or above |
| `Connect-MgGraph` hangs | Allow popups in your browser |
| Empty results | All users changed password within the threshold — try increasing the number of days |
